    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>
                <date>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> May/62</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I was thinking of writing<lb/> you in answer to your two letters
                when I got<lb/> this week your esteemed lines of <date>1<hi rend="sup"
                    >st</hi></date>. ult. You<lb/> must excuse the delay, but I understood that<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. M. D. Osorio</persName> wrote you lately, and too little<lb/>
                transpires here to tax you with a frequent cor„<lb/> respondence. I presume that he
                has given you<lb/> all information from our <placeName>Island</placeName>; however
                I<lb/> send you a slip from the “Times,” bring copy of<lb/> an address presented by
                the members of our con„<lb/>gregation to <persName>Rev. Rabbi Chumaceiro</persName>
                on his last<lb/> visit here.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Herewith please find <persName>Osorio, Wright &amp; Co.'s</persName>
                Dft.<lb/> @ 60 D/S on <persName>Dovale &amp; Co.</persName>
                <placeName>N. Y</placeName> for $66.06, for acct. due<lb/> you by me as p. annexed
                statement, and $20. in„<lb/>cluded by <persName>Mr. Correa</persName>. I could get
                no more than</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>$8. for the Pentateuch 12 mo; and there are now 3 sets<lb/> 8 vo. left. The three
                Bibles having been sold, I shall,<lb/> if convenient to you, be willing to receive
                as many<lb/> more. Perhaps also two or three copies of the Daily<lb/> Prayers in the
                cheaper bindings would also be<lb/>
                <sic>saleable</sic>. Have the goodness to send me a copy<lb/> of the first series of
                your sermons, and also name<lb/> me some others of your publications, for it
                there<lb/> are among them any which I have not read,<lb/> would like to get one or
                two. Young <persName>Mr. O.</persName> told me<lb/> some weeks ago that he had got
                several subscri„<lb/>bers for the work which you are translating, which<lb/> is more
                than I would have expected. If you can<lb/> find time please answer his letter. I
                regret to<lb/> notice your observations about the Occident. I<lb/> have not yet seen
                    <persName>Mr. Myers</persName> since, but from the<lb/> answer which he gave me
                some months ago, doubt<lb/> that he will be able to get any subscribers.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My sister left for <placeName>Panama</placeName> shortly after
                her<lb/> marriage, but I have written your remembrance<lb/> to her. My Father unties
                with me in best regards.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Respy. Yours, <persName role="author">David M. Pizal</persName></p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <table cols="2" rows="5">
                <row>
                    <cell>2 sets Pentateuch 12 mo.</cell>
                    <cell>$16.</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>1 “ Prayer Books “</cell>
                    <cell>22.87</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>2 c. Instructions</cell>
                    <cell>2.</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>2 “ Bible 18 mo.</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rend="underline">4.75</hi>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell>$45.62</cell>
                </row>
            </table>
            <p>
                <date>1862</date>
            </p>
            <p><date>Jan. 6</date> Balance in my favor $—48.</p>
            <p><date>April 30</date>, Part of <persName>Osorio, Wright &amp; Co's</persName>
                Dft.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">@60 D/S on <persName>Dovale &amp; Co.</persName>
                <placeName>N.Y.</placeName> for $66.06</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">say $46.06 @ 2% disct.    <hi rend="underline">45.14</hi>  <hi
                    rend="underline">45.62</hi></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Bal. of Dft. $20. added by <persName>Mr. M. R. A.
                Correa</persName>.</p>
        </body>
